General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play this class?

Sorceress focuses mostly on dealing damage, and it’s the closest that Lost Ark has to offer to a spell-focused mage class with elemental attributes. This class is fairly squishy and it doesn’t have anything that gets you into parties for free (like desirable synergies or good utility), but it can be very fun if you’re traditionally a mage player.

How does my identity work?

For detailed meter gain per spell, click here

Her identity consists of a single bar which can be used for either Z - Arcane Rupture or X - Blink, depending on which build you choose. Every hit you land will generate varying amounts of meter. Arcane Rupture‘s effect is different based on how much meter you have when you cast it, while using Blink allows you to teleport to your cursor while ignoring collision.

Arcane Rupture - 30%

Arcane Rupture - 100%

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

Here’s a short summary of the builds. For further information, read their respective sections of this document.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight.

Damage

What are the key pieces of my build?

Wealth & Galewind

Igniter requires Wealth Runes to build their meter. This build is not recommended without access to multiple Wealths.

Both Igniter and Reflux make good use of Galewind runes to speed up their rotation flow.

Skill Points

Skill points are important for both builds, but while Igniter can get away with enough to max 3 - 4 skills, Reflux has a more evenly spread damage distribution and needs almost every skill as high as possible.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party.

Igniter

Playstyle

Igniter mainly focuses on casting spells that deal high damage, with the rest of the kit working to empower those spells. Each build specializes in utilizing those spells in its own unique, different way.

  • Spec Igniter maximizes damage output per cast during Arcane Rupture
  • Swift Igniter maximizes cast count during Arcane Rupture

Spec Igniter

Written by Raeinor

DISCLAIMER

The Reverse Gravity variant of this build is meant for skilled players with an advanced understanding of the game, the class and all raid encounters.

If you try it and consistently underperform, consider switching back to Standard.

If the raid encounter requires a counter skill, consider switching back to Standard.

Stat Allocation

Igniter requires 100% meter in order to activate, and the damage boost from Arcane Rupture scales off of Specialization, so you need to prioritize maxing that out. Since Igniter gives you +50% Crit Damage, you’ll also want Crit on your necklace in order to capitalize on that.

Spec

Hallucination + Adrenaline allows you to take Spec/Swiftness on the Bracelet.

Spec Damage Efficiency Formula

This is how Specialization affects your damage during Arcane Rupture
Keep in mind it also increases your meter gain per hit, but this is a good indicator of how much damage you would gain from increasing the stat.

1.18 + 0.18 x Specialization stat x 2.15/699

or

1.18 + 0.18 x Specialization percentage

Example: 1700 Specialization would yield a 2.12x multiplier

Current max Specialization: 1848

Gear Set

The default Relic set is Hallucination 6-piece.

Nightmare 6-piece can be an option based on your party comp.

  • Hallucination provides higher average DPS and consistency due to its high native Crit Rate. It is at risk of running out of mana if your support isn’t good, but that can be circumvented with tripods or MP food.

  • Nightmare has more damage potential, but requires multiple Crit synergies and high MP regen uptime from a support in order to realize it. Without a good party and MP food, it is inconsistent and will perform worse than Hallucination.
    Required to play the Reverse Gravity variant.

Awakening

Enviska’s Might

Despite being a spec build, the damage of our awakening is rather low. The main use for it is triggering the Nightmare set and gaining meter at the start of a fight. It can also be used as an emergency push immunity and stagger or weak point skill, although that is not recommended due to how long it takes to cast.

Stagger

Explanation:

The damage rotation requires a full meter and must be executed before that runs out. Until you reach 100%, you can freely use all skills except for  Doomsday.

 Blaze is used as buffer between  Doomsday and  Arcane Rupture to make sure you have synergy up for your rotation and to help you time it on lower CDR gems.
Other buffer choices are  Rime Arrow, which requires you to burn your spacebar or use
Galewind on it, and  Frost’s Call, which is only available if you missed spells during meter build-up and took longer than usual to fill it.

Nightmare: You have to space out your skills in order to remain above 30% MP and maintain Magick Addiction state at least until the second  Doomsday lands at the end of Rupture. Failing to do so will result in significant damage loss.

Hallucination: You can use your skills more freely but it’s still recommended to space out your skills a bit in order to upkeep Adrenaline.

Reverse Gravity variant:

The point of this build is to trigger  Boundless MP at the point listed in the rotation above and take advantage of the CDR it provides to cycle into the next rotation faster. Once your meter is full, wait until you’re back in  Magick Addiction before starting a new rotation.

 Blaze or  Rime Arrow must be used as buffer between  Doomsday and  Arcane Rupture to make sure you can burn mana at the right pace.
 Frost’s Call is also a choice if you start with a full meter and have it available.

If you’re unable to trigger  Boundless MP due to your Support or a Summoner giving too much mana or messing up the rotation, that cycle is played the same as standard, using  Magick Addiction.

Double Doomsday

This is an integral part of your rotation, and you should practice this until you can pull it off consistently with every cast. It refers to landing two  Doomsday hits per

  Arcane Rupture, and in order to do this you need at least a Level 7 Doomsday

 Cooldown gem and proper timing. Because damage is calculated on impact, the ability must land before  Arcane Rupture ends. Refer to the GIF below.

This uses Level 7 CDR and no extra Attack Speed. This is the baseline, and it leaves you with no room to think or reposition. You can get more flexibility the higher your CDR gem is.

Animation Cancelling

All three of your main casting spells have an animation at the end that can be skipped by beginning another cast that uses an indicator. This is useful for the overall flow of rotation and for positioning if you cancel the knockback from  Explosion.

Common combinations

  •  Doomsday +  Punishing Strike (Equalized Content)
  •  Rime Arrow +  Phase Leap (Safe conditions or as a dodge mechanism)
  •  Explosion +  Punishing Strike
  •  Punishing Strike +  Rime Arrow

Swift Igniter

Written by Cleeve

DISCLAIMER

This build is not meant to be played on a budget.

 If you can’t afford the necessary setup, just pick something else.

Stat Allocation

Swift Igniter makes use of high Swiftness to maximize cast count during burst windows. In order to ensure meter generation speed and capitalize on the damage boost from Arcane Rupture, your secondary stat is Specialization.

Gear Set

Our Relic set is Nightmare 2-piece and Dominion 4-piece.

  • Nightmare 2-piece is required to reduce the mana constraints of playing a fast casting swift based build.
  • Dominion 4-piece supplies you with high uptime cooldown reduction and provides a significant damage multiplier.

3/2/2/2 Ratio

This refers to the main spells you are aiming to land during  Arcane Rupture:

3x Esoteric Reaction, 2x Doomsday, 2x Explosion, 2x Punishing Strike.

It will always be difficult to pull this off reliably in a raid scenario but it is worth practicing. Below is an example of it being done in Trixion.

This video was done with all Level 10 Cooldown Gems, and a simulated 8% Attack Speed from Yearning.

Animation Cancelling

All three of your main casting spells have an animation at the end that can be skipped by beginning another cast that uses an indicator. This is useful for the overall flow of rotation and for positioning if you cancel the knockback from  Explosion.

Common combinations

  •  Rime Arrow +  Phase Leap (Safe conditions or as a dodge mechanism)
  •  Explosion +  Punishing Strike
  •  Punishing Strike +  Rime Arrow

Playstyle

Reflux focuses on directly empowering its spells and increasing their cast count, while also allowing access to unparalleled mobility and flexibility in party compositions.

Instacast Reflux

Written by Raeinor & Acidisto

Full Crit has the highest damage potential in a rotation, while an extra Swiftness ring allows for smoother and faster gameplay. Both average similar DPS.

Stagger

For long staggers, start with delayed spells

Explanation:

Your immediate goal is to get to  Boundless MP with the opener rotation listed above and remain in that state for as long as possible.

The main drivers behind your choice of next spell to cast should be ‘How long will it take for this spell to do full damage?’ and ‘Is the target about to move or not?’.

Considering that you only have a split-second to answer these questions and make a decision, you may not always make the most optimal choice, but improving your ability to do this consistently is the best way to increase your damage.

Generally, you would want to follow the cast priority in the table above. For more advanced users, if the target moves in a predictable manner you may choose to pre-cast spells at their destination.

In order to maximize damage output, you should be constantly casting spells and looking for opportunities to fit in attacks.

Animation Cancelling

What separates a good Reflux player from a great Reflux player is their ability to cancel animations. Most skills can be animation canceled, but  Rime Arrow is the most important one. You can do this either by using your  Phase Leap (recommended) or Blink on the same spot.

Unlike  Rime Arrow, trying to animation cancel skills such as  Reverse Gravity,

  Punishing Strike or  Esoteric Reaction too early can cancel the skill entirely, causing it to go on cooldown without any damage being dealt.

Reverse Gravity

This spell has high damage output and low cooldown relative to the others, giving it the highest dps potential in your build. However, there are a few reasons why it falls off in almost every scenario.

  • Melee - Forced melee range for maximum damage.
  • Very long animation - Longest cast animation in the kit.
  • Fragmented damage distribution - Most of the damage comes from the first two hits, which reduces effectiveness when precast.
  • Less damage per cast - Requires continuous uptime to achieve its potential.

These factors cannot be accurately accounted for when measuring damage distribution with math, so there may be some differences between the chart and your personal experiences.
